oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Various excerpts, including two folk song performances
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Various excerpts including a partial dub of Ernest Tubb's Tomorrow Never Comes; an unidentified song with female vocalist; an unidentified performer performing Once I Had A Sweetheart and At Mail Call Today; and a children's performance of the nursery rhyme Frère Jacques. See also [ TR001754_2 ].
